<h1>Cacao Overnight Oats</h1>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
  <li>1/3 cup rolled oats</li>
  <li>2 teaspoons cacao powder</li>
  <li>2 teaspoons chia seeds</li>
  <li>4 teaspoons agave</li>
  <li>2 tablespoons oat milk</li>
  <li>4 tablespoons water</li>
</ul>
<h2>Steps</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Add all ingredients to a 1/2-pint mason jar.</li>
  <li>Close the lid.</li>
  <li>Shake vigorously for five seconds.</li>
  <li>Place in the fridge overnight.</li>
  <li>Eat the next day (or up to a week later) with sliced banana, chopped strawberries, frozen blueberries, and/or any combination of fruits on hand.</li>
</ol>
